President Barack Obama has announced a series of measures to enhance American energy independence and promote clean energy. These measures include the implementation of a long-term renewable fuels standard, the proposal of a rule to increase the conversion of biomass to bioenergy, and the release of a report by the Biofuels Interagency Working Group on advancing the development of a sustainable biofuels industry. Additionally, President Obama has created an Interagency Task Force on Carbon Capture and Storage to develop a federal strategy to accelerate the development and deployment of clean coal technologies. These initiatives aim to reduce dependence on foreign oil, create jobs, and combat climate change.